metadata.description:
MIJA has offered her inimitable take on a wide variety of electronic projects over the years. Accordingly, for a collaborative partner of such creative versatility, Mijaâ€™s version of the hedsTAPE sample was recorded at the Vintage Synthesizer Museum, an electronic music recording studio located in Highland Park, CA. The sample includes recordings from an original TR-808, a Moog MiniMoog Model D, a Yamaha CS-80 and more. Sounds were recorded through a Universal Audio Apollo 16. 

    This hedsTAPE was curated by MIJA during a collaborative production cycle. Each track is accompanied by a visualizer, and the entire mix is included with each mint. The talented artists featured in this mix have been chosen anonymously via heds community curation, and appear in the following order:
    
    Oshi
    Harris Cole
    Envi
    Max Fry
    Suave
    Robu
    Roto
    Evan Rolston
    Serboy
    Vaarwell
    
    Find out how to participate @ heds.app
metadata.name: hedsTAPE 11 #1
